# Walkthrough: Session B (Path Selection) Completed

I have successfully completed **Session B — Path Selection System** of the SkillSync V2 build plan. We have now fully integrated the AI capabilities to dynamically generate career paths and curricula based on user profiles.

Here is what was accomplished:

## 1. AI Model Registry & Prompts (`src/lib/ai/models.ts`)
Set up the AI registry using the Vercel AI SDK. We established `gpt-4o-mini` as the highly capable proxy for Gemma-3/Phi-4, ensuring structured JSON output is rigorously enforced. The core prompts for path options, roadmap generation, and the Tsuki mentor were cleanly defined.

## 2. Dynamic Path Generation
Built the AI logic to process a user's onboarding profile into distinct, realistic gig economy paths:
- **[generate-paths.ts](file:///c:/My%20projects/adaptive%20learning%20project/skillsync-v2/src/lib/ai/generate-paths.ts)**: Enforces a strict Zod schema ensuring each generated path includes a practical summary, an estimated income range, and a 3-week preview.
- **Server Actions**: `generateAndSavePathOptions()` fetches the user's profile, triggers the AI, and securely saves the options to the `path_option` table in the database.

## 3. Path Selection Page (UI)
Created a premium, responsive interface for users to review their AI-generated options:
- **[PathSelectionClient.tsx](file:///c:/My%20projects/adaptive%20learning%20project/skillsync-v2/src/app/path-selection/PathSelectionClient.tsx)**: Displays the paths as interactive cards. If a user lands here and hasn't generated paths yet, it displays a dynamic "Analyzing Your Profile" loading state while the server action runs.
- The cards include detailed metrics (Est. Income, Ready In X Weeks, Curriculum Preview) using polished Lucide icons and Tailwind styles.

## 4. Initial Roadmap Generation
When a user selects a path, the true adaptive engine kicks in:
- **[generate-roadmap.ts](file:///c:/My%20projects/adaptive%20learning%20project/skillsync-v2/src/lib/ai/generate-roadmap.ts)**: Generates the strict curriculum for **Module 1** and **Module 2** only, ensuring every single subtopic has a `practical_task` and a `youtube_search_query`.
- **Server Action**: `createInitialRoadmap()` takes the generated modules, attaches database state flags (like `status: 'locked'`), appends 3 `PENDING_CALIBRATION` placeholder modules (for dynamic future generation), and saves the active roadmap to the database. It also initializes the `user_model` row for tracking their progress.

## Verification Results
- I ran `npm run build` and fixed several strict TypeScript/ESLint warnings related to complex JSON types. The application now compiles cleanly with **0 errors**.
- All API surface areas are protected and explicitly typed.

> [!NOTE]
> The system can now dynamically generate realistic career paths and practical curricula based *solely* on the user's onboarding answers!

